# Windsurf Rules - MCP Tool Configuration

> **ALWAYS USE THE SVELTE AND RUST-ANALYZER MCP TOOLS FOR ALL SVELTE/RUST TASKS**

---

## Svelte MCP Server (Official)

This project uses the official Svelte MCP server for all Svelte/SvelteKit development.

### Available Tools

#### 1. list-sections
- **Use FIRST** to discover all available documentation sections
- Returns structured list with titles, use_cases, and paths
- When asked about Svelte or SvelteKit topics, **ALWAYS use this tool at the start of the chat**

#### 2. get-documentation
- Retrieves full documentation content for specific sections
- Accepts single or multiple sections
- After calling `list-sections`, **MUST analyze the use_cases field** and fetch ALL relevant documentation sections

#### 3. svelte-autofixer
- **MUST use this tool whenever writing Svelte code before sending to the user**
- Analyzes Svelte code and returns issues/suggestions
- Keep calling until no issues or suggestions are returned

#### 4. playground-link
- Generates a Svelte Playground link with provided code
- Only call after user confirmation
- **NEVER use if code was written to files in the project**

### Tool Usage Rules

**When working with Svelte/SvelteKit code:**

1. Start with `list-sections` to find relevant documentation
2. Call `get-documentation` for ALL sections matching the use case
3. Use `svelte-autofixer` on any generated code before presenting to user
4. Offer `playground-link` only for code not written to project files

### Documentation Categories

| Category | Use Cases |
|----------|-----------|
| **CLI** (`cli/*`) | Project setup, adding features, migration, testing setup |
| **Svelte** (`svelte/*`) | Core reactivity, components, runes, transitions |
| **SvelteKit** (`kit/*`) | Routing, data loading, form actions, adapters, deployment |
| **AI** (`ai/*`) | MCP server setup, skills, subagents |
| **Legacy** (`svelte/legacy-*`) | Migration from Svelte 3/4 to 5 |

### Key Runes (Svelte 5)

| Rune | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `$state` | Declare reactive state |
| `$derived` | Compute derived values |
| `$effect` | Run side effects |
| `$props` | Component props declaration |
| `$bindable` | Two-way binding |
| `$inspect` | Debug reactive values |

### Critical Patterns

**Always use `svelte-autofixer` for:**
- New `.svelte` files
- Modified `.svelte` files
- Component props/interfaces
- Event handlers
- Runes usage
- Snippet/render patterns

